<inglise> - Practical Aspects: the physical conduct of any of the exposure referred to in Article 1 (2) and any supporting aspects including handling and use of radiological equipment, and the assessment of technical and physical parameters including radiation doses, calibration and maintenance of equipment, preparation and administration of radio-pharmaceuticals and the development of films. </inglise>
<eesti> teostus - artikli 1 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud kiirituse p&otilde;hjustamine ja k&otilde;ik abitoimingud, sealhulgas radioloogiaseadmete k&auml;sitsemine ja kasutamine, tehniliste ja f&uuml;&uuml;sikaliste n&auml;itajate, sealhulgas kiirgusdooside hindamine, seadmete taatlus ja hooldus, radiofarmpreparaatide valmistamine ja manustamine ning piltide ilmutamine; </eesti>
<inglise> - Practitioner: a medical doctor, dentist or other health professional, who is entitled to take clinical responsibility for an individual medical exposure in accordance with national requirements. </inglise>
<eesti> radioloogiaprotseduuri tegev arst - arst, hambaarst v&otilde;i muu tervishoiut&ouml;&ouml;taja, kellel on siseriiklike n&otilde;uete kohaselt &otilde;igus v&otilde;tta endale kliiniline vastutus &uuml;ksikisiku meditsiinikiirituse eest; </eesti>
