<inglise> Justification </inglise>
<eesti> P&otilde;hjendamine </eesti>
<inglise> 1. </inglise>
<eesti> 1. </eesti>
<inglise> Medical exposure referred to in Article 1 (2) shall show a sufficient net benefit, weighing the total potential diagnostic or therapeutic benefits it produces, including the direct health benefits to an individual and the benefits to society, against the individual detriment that the exposure might cause, taking into account the efficacy, benefits and risks of available alternative techniques having the same objective but involving no or less exposure to ionizing radiation. </inglise>
